# dockerignore — the ONE ignore file for every repo-root-context Docker build: the desktop
# builder image (`desktop/docker/Dockerfile`) AND the deploy image (`deploy/common/Dockerfile`,
# see `deploy/README.md`). Docker resolves `.dockerignore` from the CONTEXT ROOT, not next to
# the Dockerfile — a per-Dockerfile ignore file needs `buildx build --ignorefile`, which the
# classic (non-buildx) `docker build`/`docker compose build` used for local dev and CI does not
# support. So this is it: one file, every driver, no drift.
#
# Everything excluded here is either regenerated inside the image (target/, dist/,
# node_modules/) or irrelevant to the build (VCS, editor config, the artifact tarballs
# themselves).

# VCS + editor state
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
.DS_Store

# Rust build artifacts (regenerated by cargo inside the container)
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk

# Node/pnpm build artifacts (regenerated by pnpm/vite inside the container)
**/node_modules/
ui/dist/
ui/build/
**/.pnpm-debug.log*

# Existing desktop binaries / artifacts — never bake the output back into the input
desktop/docker/*.tar
**/*.AppImage
**/*.deb
**/*.rpm
**/*.snap
**/*.msi
**/*.exe

# Test artifacts + caches
ui/test-results/
ui/coverage/
**/.vitest-cache/
**/.vite-cache/

# Sessions are working logs, never build inputs. NOTE: `docs/` itself is NOT excluded —
# `rust/crates/assets/build.rs` embeds `docs/skills/*/SKILL.md` + `docs/testing/**/*.md` at
# build time (panics if a skills dir lacks SKILL.md), and `lb-assets` is pulled transitively
# by the shell via `lb-host`. The whole `docs/` tree is ~10 MB; keep it.
docs/sessions/
**/sessions/

# The Nextra doc-site is ~1 GB (node_modules) and unrelated to the binary build.
doc-site/

# Other top-level workspaces neither build touches
app/shell/

# docker/postgres/ carries the demo-dataset generator the DEPLOY image needs at runtime
# (deploy/common/Dockerfile copies these into /opt/lazybones/seed/ — see seed-demo-sqlite.sh) —
# allow just those files; the rest (compose stack, .env, __pycache__, init SQL) is dev-only.
docker/postgres/
!docker/postgres/seed.py
!docker/postgres/generators.py
!docker/postgres/inventory.py
!docker/postgres/tags.py
!docker/postgres/sinks_sqlite.py
!docker/postgres/seed-demo-sqlite.sh
